  "title": "Manager (Investment)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform in-depth research and analysis, including market research, competitor research and financial metrics</li><li>Lead/support in sourcing and evaluation of investment opportunities</li><li>Lead/support end-to-end investment transactions including origination, deal evaluation and structuring, financial analysis including financial modelling, and preparation of reports to board and investment committee.</li><li>Develop and maintain portfolio analytics dashboards and databases</li><li>Engage with overseas offices to identify gaps related to data, analyse portfolio data trends and provide recommendations for decision making</li><li>Preparing the investment reports to Beijing HQ</li><li>Liaise with Beijing HQ effectively, take charge of processing of incoming correspondences, distribution, follow-up and response.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Min Degree in Accountancy/ACCA or equivalent</li><li>At least 5 years of relevant experience</li><li>Team player with strong communication skills, meticulous, numeric, ability to handle large dataset and able to work in a fast-paced environment.</li></ul>",
